Title: On the Entropy of a Quantum Field in the 2 + 1 Dimensional Spinning
  Black Holes
Authors: Min-Ho Lee, Hyeong-Chan Kim, and Jae Kwan Kim (KAIST in KOREA)
Comments: Title changed, Major corrections
Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B388 (1996) 487-493
\\
  We calculate the entropy of a scalar field in a rotating black hole in 2 + 1
dimension. In the Hartle-Hawking state the entropy is proportional to the
horizon area, but diverges linearly in $\sqrt{h}$, where $h$ is the radial
cut-off. In WKB approximation the superradiant modes do not contribute to the
entropy.
